# SWT dashboard live event stream (per-session JSONL emitted by the CLI;
# session-local state, not project artifact).
#
# Also ignore `.swt-planning/`: the dashboard's Init flow creates
# `.swt-planning/PROJECT.md` + `STATE.md` in the daemon's cwd, which during
# local development of SWT itself is the source repo root. SWT v3 development
# uses `.vbw-planning/` (VBW-driven), so `.swt-planning/` here is always
# dev-test detritus and should never enter git. When SWT-on-SWT dogfooding
# lands, this entry needs revisiting.
.swt-planning/

# Changesets internals
.changeset/.changes-*/

# Local research artefact (kept out of git unless intentionally added)
compass_artifact_*.md

# Local working copy of VBW (out of git; not part of SWT)
vibe-better-with-claude-code-vbw-main/

# Non-production scratch / experiment files (anywhere in the tree, all
# current and future contents). Keep out of git so the repo stays
# focused on shippable code.
non_production_files/

# --- VBW planning state (granular, post-pivot) ---
#
# `.vbw-planning/` itself is TRACKED on v3-foundation — it carries the
# v3 design plans (PROJECT.md, REQUIREMENTS.md, ROADMAP.md, STATE.md,
# phases/, research/, etc.). Only the runtime state files inside it
# are .gitignored — they're regenerated on every VBW invocation.
.vbw-planning/.context-usage
.vbw-planning/.cost-ledger.json
.vbw-planning/.vbw-context
.vbw-planning/.cache/
.vbw-planning/.metrics/
.vbw-planning/.notification-log.jsonl
.vbw-planning/.session-log.jsonl
.vbw-planning/.claude-md-migrated
.vbw-planning/.skills-section-stripped
.vbw-planning/.todo-flat-migrated

# Per-phase compiled context files — regenerated by compile-context.sh
.vbw-planning/phases/*/.context-*.md

# Cloned reference: SWT v2.3.5 source had its own .git history; the
# clone lived here for read-only recon during M1 planning. Now that
# v3-foundation IS v2.3.5 + v3 plans, the clone is no longer needed,
# but the rule is harmless if a future contributor re-clones it.
.vbw-planning/research/swt-v2-source/
